<item>
            <title>[TINKERPOP-2610] NumberHelper can return values in the form of their original type smaller than int</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP-2610</link>
                <project id="12316520" key="TINKERPOP">TinkerPop</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;NumberHelper&lt;/tt&gt; converts smaller number types like short/byte to int after applying a function to them. It was thought that this was just the way things worked on the JVM but all we needed to do was cast to the appropriate type. Didn&apos;t want to fix this along existing release branches because it could create some subtle breaking change in equality. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
